                     <interp inst="def1-978-18450407" type="surname" value="CORNISH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-978-18450407" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JAMES CORNISH</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-978-18450407" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-978-18450407" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-978-18450407" type="age" value="21"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-978-18450407" type="surname" value="CANNON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-978-18450407" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM CANNON</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18450407-978-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18450407-978-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18450407-978-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="housebreaking"></interp>feloniously breaking and entering a building, within the curtilage of the dwelling-house of <persName id="t18450407-name-1069" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1069" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1069" type="surname" value="COSSAR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1069" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-978-offence-1 t18450407-name-1069"></join>George Cossar</persName>, on the <rs id="t18450407-cd-84" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-978-offence-1 t18450407-cd-84"></join>9th of March</rs>, at <placeName id="t18450407-geo-18">
                        <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18450407-978-offence-1 t18450407-geo-18"></join>Walthamstow</placeName>, and stealing therein, 1 basket, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 15 chisels, 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 11 guages, 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 12 screw-drivers, 12<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 2 gouges, 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 19 brad-awls, 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 4 saws, 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.; 30 planes, 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.; 7 plough irons, 9<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; and great variety of other tools, his property.—2nd <hi rend="smallCaps">COUNT</hi>, calling it a shop.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">CANNON</hi> pleaded 
<rs id="t18450407-978-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18450407-978-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18450407-978-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="pleadedGuilty"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi>, and received a good character.—<hi rend="italic">Rrecommended to mercy.</hi>
                  </rs> Aged 21.—<hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18450407-978-punishment-156" type="punishmentDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-978-punishment-156" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-978-punishment-156" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>
                        <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-978-18450407 t18450407-978-punishment-156"></join>Confined Two Years</rs>.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1070" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1070" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1070" type="surname" value="COSSAR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1070" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE COSSAR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter, and live at Walthamstow. On Sunday, the 9th of March, I saw my tools safe in my workshop, which ii within a few yards of my dwelling-house—the dwelling-house and work<lb></lb>shop are all inclosed by a pale fence—both have doors opening into tne yard—I missed the tools on Monday morning at seven o'clock—the door of the workshop had been forced open, apparently with a chisel—I saw my tools again on the Saturday following at we Police-court.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> I suppose you had not ustd your tools on Sunday? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No-they were locked up in my chest, but I looked into the chest—I found the chest broken open.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1071" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1071" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1071" type="surname" value="ELVIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1071" type="given" value="THOMAS WILLIAM"></interp>THOMAS WILLIAM ELVIDGE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Worrall and Pown<lb></lb>all, pawnbrokers. I produce a smoothing-plane, twtnty-six chisels, and fifty-five tools in a basket, which were pawned with roe on Monday, tae 10th, I think—I also produce two planes pawned the name of charles Jones—I do not know by whom.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1072" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1072" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1072" type="surname" value="MINOAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1072" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MINOAY</persName>
                  </hi>. A chisel was brought to me by the policeman—I know Cannon, and am quite certain he had that chisel at the time he worked for me.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184504070192"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1073" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1073" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1073" type="surname" value="NICHOLL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1073" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM NICHOLL</persName>
                  </hi>. I was a policeman at this time, and took the prisoners into custody on Wednesday night, the 12th of March, about nine o'clock—each had a bundle—I went up and said to Cannon, "What have you got here?"—he said, "Tools"—I said, "What tools?"—he said, "Tools I use in my work"—he said, "I have been at work at the docks"—I said, "At the docks at this time of night?"—he said, "If you will go to my master, Mr. Mingay, he will tell you it is right"—I took them to the station—I found six planes in Cannon's bundle—I did not search Cornish's bundle—another constable stopped him, but at the station I observed something bulky in Cornish's pockets—I examined them, and found nine planes—he said, "They are not mine, I am only carrying them for Cannon."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1074" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1074" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1074" type="surname" value="BRICE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1074" type="given" value="AUGUSTUS"></interp>AUGUSTUS BRICE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I was at the station-house when the bundle was taken from Cannon—I observed he was bulky, and asked what he had got there—he said, "Feel and see"—I felt and found seven planes, seven plough-irons, and a broken chisel on him—he said he had brought them from the other side of Chelmsford—Cornish said he bad nothing to do with it, he was employed by Cannon to carry them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1075" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1075" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1075" type="surname" value="WOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1075" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WOOD</persName>
                  </hi>. I was with Nicholl at the time the prisoners were stopped—Cornish had this bundle in his hand—I asked what he had got there—he said they were tools—I asked him where he got them from—he said he had been to fetch them out of pawn—I asked where—he said he was a coach-builder and was going into Rosemary-lane to work—the bundle contains five planes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Who was present when he said this about Rosemary-lane 1 A. Nobody; he said so in Commercial-road—the other two officers were nine or ten yards before me with the other prisoner—I did not hear what Cornish said at the station.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450407-name-1076" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1076" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1076" type="surname" value="COSSAR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450407-name-1076" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK COSSAR</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the prosecutor's son. Cornish has worked with me some months ago—I have known Cannon work at a wheelwright's shop close by—I have seen them together on the forest close by, several times—Cornish has not worked in our workshop—he worked as a sawyer—he has been in the shop but not with any of the tools—I know these planes found in Cornish's bundle—they have my name on them—I know all the tools in this bundle—these found in Cornish's pocket have my father's name on them—they are all his, and part of the property missing—we never sell our tools—I have examined the rest of the property found on Cannon—they are all my father's.</p>
               <p>
